The paper focuses on analyzing the usage and impact of a social feature introduced by GitHub, which is relevant to software engineering (cs.SE) and social computing (cs.SI). The analysis involves processing a large amount of data, which could fall under the category of cybernetics (cs.CY) and software development (cs.SD). Additionally, the paper also touches upon the impact of the feature on discussions, which could relate to human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
